Rules.InvariantScript:
" Guidance
  • Example use of the EmailFns below.
  • It assumes the EmailFn component is inserted somewhere in the app (e.g. Loading screen).
  • In order to work, the EmailFn's properties AppRelease and AppTitle need setting to APP_RELEASE and APP_TITLE.
  • Note these two guidance components are only visible when APP_RELEASE.Type = 'Dev'. "

" With({ Email: EmailFn.Builder({ To: 'jonathan.warman@apacheix.co.uk', Subject: 'Test Email', Header: 'Someting here', Content: '

You've recieved this email because of X.

Details

Some more text. Please do X Y Z.' & '

' & EmailFn.Button('Single', '', 120, '#009900') & '
' & EmailFn.ButtonRow([ EmailFn.Button('Done', '', 100, '#0000FF'), EmailFn.Button('Clear', '', 150, '#FF0000') ]), MinWidth: 550}) }, Office365Outlook.SendEmailV2(Email.To, Email.Subject, Email.Body) ); "

ControlPropertyState.AutoRuleBindingString:
{ To: "jonathan.warman@apacheix.co.uk", Subject: "Test Email", Header: "", Content: "

Put your email content here. ", MinWidth: 550 }

Switch(Self.AppRelease.Type,
    "Error",    "PowerApps maker error: AppRelease not set.", 
    "Dev",      "<<Dev>> " & Subject,
    "Alpha",    "<<Alpha/Test>> " & Subject,
    "Beta",     Subject,
    "Prod",     Subject,
    "PowerApps maker error: AppRelease.Type not known: " & AppRelease.Type
)

"

" & Attributes & " width=" & 600*SizePct & " height=" & 190*SizePct & " src='data:image/jpeg;base64," & ""

"
" & Switch(Self.AppRelease.Type, "Dev", "

Dev Environment

Note Dev app's data resides in the dev environment, all emails come to the person testing the app (i.e. you!).", "Alpha", "

Dev 'Alpha' Environment

Note an Alpha app's data resides in the dev environment, but emails are sent to the individuals (with this warning message)." ) & // End Switch "

Reminder

" & Content & "

This is an automated message from " & Self.AppTitle & " app.
Send bugs or feature requests to feedback@apacheix.dev.

" & Self.ApacheLogoImg(0.2) // 600 x 190 & "
"
